Create simple shell for linux usig processes fork(),wait(),execvp() and exit().
Your solution need to support the following commands(as well as their optional parameters):
a. ls
b. pwd 
c. date 
d. cal 
e. cp
f. mkdir 
g. rmdir 
h. rm 
i. cat 
j. mv 
k. ps 
l. touch
m. echo
n. sleep

If the last parameter of a command is "&" , the command should run in the background, otherwise it should run in the foreground. 
